<h1 align="center">Forex Trading</h1>
<p>
Forex (Foreign Exchange) market is one of the largest and decentralized forms of global marketplace that facilitates trading of various national currencies worth over trillions of dollars in a day. Some broker platforms also allow traders to participate in commodity markets such as trading gold and silver. The Forex market is an essential element of International Business, where foremost participants are engaged in transferring large sums of monetary units for export-import, cross-border investment as well as debt and repayments. It is a 24/5 market, expanded across the globe where major financial centers like Tokyo, London and New York act as hubs for trading Pound against Dollar or Ringgit against Rupee. As an open and free market, the supply and demand for national currencies act as a mechanism to determine the relative values of various national currencies. Institutional and private traders from all over the world participate in Forex market to buy and sell these currencies in order to make large sums of leveraged profits.
</p>
